1️⃣ Attack Vector (AV)
How the attacker reaches the vulnerable system
Value	Meaning
AV:N	Network (over the internet)
AV:A	Adjacent network (same Wi-Fi / LAN)
AV:L	Local system access
AV:P	Physical access required


2️⃣ Attack Complexity (AC)
How difficult the attack is
Value	Meaning
AC:L	Low complexity (easy to exploit)
AC:H	High complexity (needs special conditions)



3️⃣ Privileges Required (PR)
Does attacker need login access?
Value	Meaning
PR:N	No authentication required
PR:L	Low privileges (normal user)
PR:H	High privileges (admin access)

	
4️⃣ User Interaction (UI)
Does another user need to interact?
Value	Meaning
UI:N	No user interaction
UI:R	User interaction required


5️⃣ Scope (S)
Does the vulnerability affect other systems/components?
Value	Meaning
S:U	Scope Unchanged
S:C	Scope Changed


6️⃣ Confidentiality Impact (C)
Does it expose sensitive data?
Value	Meaning
C:N	No impact
C:L	Low data exposure
C:H	High data exposure
Example:
SQL Injection → C:H
________________________________________







7️⃣ Integrity Impact (I)
Can attacker modify data?
Value	Meaning
I:N	No impact
I:L	Low modification
I:H	High modification
Example:
Database modification → I:H
________________________________________
8️⃣ Availability Impact (A)
Can attacker crash or stop the system?
Value	Meaning
A:N	No impact
A:L	Low impact
A:H	High impact






